    <question>
        <prompt>The Scopes Trial's broader significance was its representation of:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Scientific debate only</option>
            <option letter="b">Modernism versus traditionalism in American culture</option>
            <option letter="c">Educational funding issues</option>
            <option letter="d">State rights concerns</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The 1925 Scopes "Monkey" Trial represented the broader cultural conflict between modernism and traditionalism in American society. While ostensibly about teaching evolution, the trial symbolized deeper tensions between urban and rural values, science and religion, and traditional beliefs versus modern ideas. The extensive media coverage made it a defining moment in the cultural battles of the 1920s.</explanation>
    </question>
